:—gregarious or sometimes paired, deeply immersed in the litter and needles, in silver fir forests. The studied specimens have always been found in mountainous silver firs on calcareous soil, in sites notoriously rich in other phlegmacioid species. So far known only from Northeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[883,936,1778,1804]" name="Italy" pageId="6" pageNumber="231">Italy</collectingCountry>
.
